import React, { useEffect } from "react"; const HTMLComponent = () => { useEffect(() => { function myMenuFunction() { var i = document.getElementById("navMenu"); if (i.className === "nav-menu") { i.className += " responsive"; } else { i.className = "nav-menu"; } } var a = document.getElementById("loginBtn"); var b = document.getElementById("registerBtn"); var x = document.getElementById("login"); var y = document.getElementById("register"); function login() { x.style.left = "4px"; y.style.right = "-520px"; a.className += " white-btn"; b.className = "btn"; x.style.opacity = 1; y.style.opacity = 0; } function register() { x.style.left = "-510px"; y.style.right = "5px"; a.className = "btn"; b.className += " white-btn"; x.style.opacity = 0; y.style.opacity = 1; } }, []); // empty dependency array to run the effect only once return ( <> Ludiflex | Login & Registration
